      "content": "that's getting closer to the tone i wanted. can you lean more into the idea that their lack of structure actually makes them dangerous or volatile? like the explorer is explaining to his men that without our strict laws and authority, these people are basically just driven by instinct rather than reason, and that's why we have to impose our rule to keep things from descending into chaos.",
